Sentencas: This article summarizes the progress of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells materials including electrolyte and electrode, and discusses the effect of grain boundary, phase surface and structure morphology on process and performance, especially analyzes and compares the nutual contradictory effect of grain-boundary on oxide ionic conductivity of the electrolyte.
Titulo: Review of progress in materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Some recommendations of R&D are proposed also.
Titulo: Review of progress in materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
